data.title: Unimpressed with the wurst plate.
data.text: The wurst was on the low side of average; sweet potato fries were ok. The place was crazy busy on a Saturday morning, and the energy was upbeat and fun. I think I may have made a poor menu choice; the breakfast food I saw being served looked better....

data.title: i liked it i like it alot
data.text: great breakfast taco's this place is reasonably priced and the latte was excellent, it is right downtown in a great location

data.title: Cool Place on a Hot Day
data.text: We stopped here to cool down on a hot Texas afternoon while traveling in this area.  The ice cream was excellent as were the cold drinks that we enjoyed.  Nice, casual atmosphere with many people on internet or playing board games.  The kind of place where you can linger awhile.  Order at the counter and they will call you when your order is ready kind of place.  After this cross the street and check out the library.  It was another place to spend some time on a hot day.  We were able to print our boarding passes for our return flight from the library"s computer for 10 cents a sheet.

data.title: Round Rock's answer to the Chain Coffe shops
data.text: Everything goes better with Star Co.  Grab breakfast, lunch, a snack or just a cup of coffee.  Come to talk or read or work on your lap top.  This is one if the cool places in quaint downtown Round Rock, and you won't be disappointed.  The food is great and the service us friendly.

data.title: Great place and atmosphere
data.text: First time to visit while on vacation but would definitely go back! The coffee is wonderful and husband had the ice cream which he said was amazing. They serve food as well and while we didn't try it it looked very appetizing.

data.title: Not bad, not great
data.text:
What I liked:
Ordered at counter - young woman was friendly
Dining area had a nice warm feel and plenty of space
Background music/noise was at a nice level - would be a good place for a one-on-one meeting
Strawberry ice cream cone for dessert was tasty

Not so much:
Chicken melt sandwich was ok...I guess.  Chicken was overcooked - not much flavor
Had to wait at counter for quite a while to order - was a couple of folks in front of me

All in all an average experience.  Next time I'm in town I probably won't go there, except for dessert or coffee.

data.title: Long wait for average food and coffee
data.text: Love the atmosphere; very laid back and kinda hippy in feel. Waited a long time even though it wasn't lunchtime. Had latte, which was average, and vegetarian rice bowl, which was a step above airplane food. Hubby had veggie omelet; also average.

data.title: Coffee was good enough, could do way better with the space?
data.text: It was a cold day (rare here, right? LOL) and the cafe just wasn't a warm or welcoming environment.  Diner-ish quality tables and chairs.  One big open room.  Decent service but nothing to write home about.  Great location.  I prefer little seating areas and padded booths or furniture - they're much cozier.

data.title: Great Coffee!
data.text: I came in for a coffee and the gal at the register was super helpful with her suggestions and made me a great latte! I also discovered they have a full food menu and service breakfast all day. I'll be back for sure!

data.title: Nice meeting place
data.text:
This had been nestled in downtown Round Rock for years, but at a slightly different location.  The new address (which has been open since at least the start of the year), retains the charm of the original spot.  Chairs and tables are placed in a spacious arrangements to provide a nice meeting area, and there’s a private room in the back which can be secured for more private functions.

The coffee and the book lending library still make this a place to relax.  One addition has been the availability of Amy’s Ice Cream, which in my experience hasn’t been previously available in Round Rock.

Because Star Co is located right next to the parking garage, you don’t have to go too far away from your car.  This makes it a nice intimate place for any social gathering.

data.title: Great coffee
data.text: Breakfast tacos are high for a small breakfast. The venue has a cafeteria look, with the chairs and empty feel, but some nice features such as the front window seats, outdoor seating.

data.title: Nice Location. Period.
data.text: Star Co lost their good menu and atmosphere when they moved to this location.  Drink selections are quite limited to coffee drinks; they used to have Italian sodas, sandwiches, and other items besides coffee.

data.title: Uninspired new space
data.text:
Star Coffee Co has been located in downtown Round Rock for several years. For some unknown reason they closed their previous location, took a few months off, then reopened across the street. The new location is utterly uninspired. Boring black vinyl chairs, rough lighting, not much decor... it doesn't add up to a space I want to stay in for any length of time.

The coffee is pretty good. Not amazing, but good enough. The service has been a bit slow each time I've visited. There are better (non-chain) options for coffee in Round Rock.

data.title: Feels Like Hipsterland
data.text: I liked this place in the old location and I had high hopes for the new location plan. At the new location, from the time I walked through the door some hipster couple was on their computers, their little out of control child jumped in our way and blocked it. The parents did nothing, so I walked around the kid. They then gave me dirty looks, like I should have been blessed that their little brat was acting out towards me. We finally got into the place and I ordered my kid and I some ice cream. A small scoop of a basic ice cream for each of us. It was $7. That's pretty steep for a couple scoops of ice cream. I've been back by, but every time it's full of hipsters/yuppies. I was looking forward to a collective place down town to enjoy a coffee house environment, but the first few tries have ruined it for me.

data.title: New location, same great people!
data.text: Star is a great place to be!  The new location is up and running and they're working out the kinks.  Great new menu.  Still some of the same great offerings - breakfast tacos, bottomless mug of coffee.  Wonderful place to get work done or just meet with friends to chat for hours.  Family friendly.  Prices are easy on the wallet.

data.title: Great place to meet with friends
data.text: We came in for lunch after a meeting.  They have indoor and outdoor seating, wifi, food, lattes and Amy's ice cream.   Order at the counter they bring it to you.  A great find!
